      &lt;p&gt;Look the world through holes.&lt;br&gt;Ah, human are beautiful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;Commentary&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Commentary&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Commentary&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Commentary&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;This work consists of three peep boxes. The author expresses a “sparkle” of the mental world. Each of the peep boxes is named “pray or entrance,” “memory,” “dialogue.” Those three are supposed to watch in order. In “pray or entrance,” a tiny light that looks dark unless you look closely. In “memory,” multiple bright lights make as if abstract painting in the box. In “dialogue,” Your eye is illuminated and reflected on a wall in the box.&lt;br&gt;Through those works and a caption, the author encourages observers to consider the aesthetics of the mental. And, he claims the mental world of the human is beautiful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;mute&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#mute&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;mute&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;mute&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;mute exhibits our work with “minimal and analog aesthetics as theme.&lt;/p&gt;
